            whatIsIt: "CJC-1295 (No DAC), also correctly known as Modified GRF 1-29, is a synthetic version of your body's natural Growth Hormone-Releasing Hormone (GHRH). It is designed to signal your pituitary gland to release more of your own natural growth hormone. The 'No DAC' part is crucial: it means it does not have the Drug Affinity Complex attached. Without the DAC, the peptide has a short half-life, meaning it causes a massive, natural 'pulse' of growth hormone and then quickly leaves your system, perfectly mimicking how your body naturally releases GH.",
