                FAQItem(question: "Why do I feel worse after starting oral KPV?", answer: "If you have a bacterial overgrowth (SIBO) or a yeast infection (Candida) in your gut, KPV will start killing those pathogens. When they die, they release endotoxins into your bloodstream, causing a Herxheimer reaction (fatigue, brain fog, mild nausea). This means the peptide is working. It usually passes in 3-5 days."),
