                FAQItem(question: "Is Tirzepatide the same thing as Mounjaro and Zepbound?", answer: "Yes. Tirzepatide is the name of the actual peptide molecule. Mounjaro is the brand name for Type 2 Diabetes. Zepbound is the brand name for weight loss."),
                FAQItem(question: "Why is it better than Ozempic (Semaglutide)?", answer: "Ozempic only targets one receptor (GLP-1). Tirzepatide targets two (GLP-1 and GIP). The addition of GIP not only increases the amount of weight lost but also significantly reduces the nausea and fatigue that many people experience on Ozempic."),
                FAQItem(question: "Do I have to stay on it forever?", answer: "If you do not change your lifestyle, yes. The drug fixes your metabolic signaling while you are on it. If you stop, your old appetite will return. To transition off, you must have built strict habits around protein intake, portion control, and weightlifting, and you should taper the dose down very slowly."),
