            deepDive: "AOD-9604 is a 16-amino acid peptide identical to the C-terminal sequence of human growth hormone (residues 176-191), with the addition of a tyrosine residue at the N-terminus (Tyr-hGH176-191).\n\nThe Tyrosine Addition: The addition of tyrosine was a crucial modification by Metabolic Pharmaceuticals. It stabilizes the peptide, preventing rapid degradation and making it significantly more robust than the standard 'Frag 176-191.'\n\nPharmacokinetics: Despite the stabilization, it has an incredibly short plasma half-life of approximately 3 to 4 minutes. However, the lipolytic cascade it triggers in adipocytes lasts for hours.\n\nMechanism Deep Dive:\nAOD-9604 mimics the lipolytic (fat-burning) actions of full HGH without binding to the HGH receptor.\n\n1. Beta-3 Adrenergic Receptors: Research indicates that AOD-9604 exerts its fat-burning effects by upregulating the beta-3 adrenergic receptors on white adipose tissue.\n\n2. Lipolysis: By stimulating these receptors, it activates hormone-sensitive lipase (HSL), the enzyme responsible for breaking down stored triglycerides into free fatty acids and glycerol.\n\n3. Inhibition of Lipogenesis: Simultaneously, AOD-9604 downregulates the enzymes involved in lipogenesis (the creation of new fat), specifically acetyl-CoA carboxylase.\n\n4. No IGF-1 Activation: Because it lacks the binding domain of the full HGH molecule, AOD-9604 cannot bind to the HGH receptor in the liver. Therefore, it does not stimulate IGF-1 production, meaning no cell proliferation, no organ growth, and no insulin resistance.\n\nClinical Trial Summary:\n- Obesity Trials: Metabolic Pharmaceuticals ran six human clinical trials (Phase 1 and 2) involving over 900 patients. In a 12-week Phase 2b trial, patients on 1mg/day lost an average of 2.6 kg, compared to 0.8 kg in the placebo group.\n- Osteoarthritis: AOD-9604 is currently being investigated for osteoarthritis. Animal models show intra-articular injections promote cartilage repair and reduce joint inflammation.\n\nAntagonism with Insulin: The lipolytic cascade triggered by AOD-9604 is highly sensitive to insulin. Even a small spike in insulin (from eating a carbohydrate-rich meal) will completely halt the release of free fatty acids, rendering the peptide useless.",
