                FAQItem(question: "Why do people say to take it before MOTS-c?", answer: "Think of your mitochondria like a car engine. If the engine is leaking oil and broken (cardiolipin damage), you don't want to press the gas pedal to the floor (MOTS-c). You want to fix the oil leak first (SS-31), and then press the gas pedal."),
