            subtitle: "The Ultimate Muscle Hyperplasia Peptide",
            whatIsIt: "IGF-1 LR3 (Insulin-like Growth Factor-1 Long Arginine 3) is a highly modified, synthetic version of the naturally occurring IGF-1 hormone. In the human body, Growth Hormone (GH) travels to the liver, which then produces IGF-1. IGF-1 is the actual hormone responsible for muscle growth and tissue repair. By injecting IGF-1 LR3 directly, you bypass the liver entirely. The 'LR3' modification makes this peptide roughly three times more potent than natural IGF-1 and extends its active life in the body from a few minutes to over a day.",
