                FAQItem(question: "Why do I feel so hungry after injecting?", answer: "IGF-1 LR3 pulls glucose out of your blood and into your muscles. This drop in blood sugar triggers your brain to release hunger signals. You must eat carbs when this happens."),
                FAQItem(question: "Can I reconstitute it with normal Bacteriostatic Water?", answer: "Yes, but it will degrade faster. If you use BAC water, try to use the vial within 14-21 days. If you want it to last for months, reconstitute with Acetic Acid (AA) and then dilute with BAC water in the syringe right before injecting."),
                FAQItem(question: "Is it better than HGH?", answer: "They serve different purposes. HGH is better for fat loss, joint repair, and anti-aging, and can be run for months. IGF-1 LR3 is strictly for rapid, massive muscle growth and nutrient partitioning, and can only be run for a few weeks at a time."),
