            subtitle: "The Stem Cell Activator",
            whatIsIt: "PEG-MGF (Pegylated Mechano Growth Factor) is a synthetic version of a naturally occurring peptide in your muscles. When you lift heavy weights and damage your muscle fibers, your body naturally produces Mechano Growth Factor (MGF) to repair the damage. MGF's job is to wake up dormant muscle stem cells (satellite cells) so they can fix the tear. Natural MGF only lasts in the body for a few minutes. Scientists added a chemical shield called 'PEG' (Polyethylene Glycol) to the peptide, which protects it from being destroyed by the body, extending its lifespan from minutes to several days.",
            howItWorks: "Imagine your muscle is a brick wall. When you work out, you knock some bricks out of the wall. Your body has a pile of spare bricks sitting nearby (stem cells), but they are asleep. MGF is the alarm clock that wakes up the spare bricks and tells them to go fix the wall. By injecting PEG-MGF, you are sounding a massive, continuous alarm that wakes up millions of spare bricks, allowing your body to repair the wall much faster and make it thicker than it was before.",
