            subtitle: "The SARM / Myostatin Inhibitor Hybrid",
            whatIsIt: "YK-11 is one of the most unique and misunderstood compounds in the biohacking world. It is marketed and sold as a SARM (Selective Androgen Receptor Modulator), but chemically, its structure is actually closer to a synthetic steroid (a DHT derivative). What makes YK-11 famous is its dual mechanism: it binds to androgen receptors to build muscle (like a SARM/steroid), but it also forces muscle cells to produce more Follistatin, which in turn blocks Myostatin. It is essentially a steroid and a myostatin inhibitor rolled into one oral compound.",
