                FAQItem(question: "Do I inject it into my fat or my muscle?", answer: "Muscle (Intramuscular / IM). L-Carnitine is a large molecule and the volume is usually high (1mL). Injecting it into subcutaneous fat will cause a painful, red lump that takes weeks to go away."),
                FAQItem(question: "I'm on a Keto diet. How do I spike my insulin to load the L-Carnitine?", answer: "This is the paradox of L-Carnitine. If you are strictly keto, you cannot spike your insulin with carbs. Some advanced users will use a fast-acting whey protein isolate to get a mild insulin spike, or they accept that the loading process will be much slower and less efficient."),
                FAQItem(question: "What is ALCAR? Is it the same thing?", answer: "Acetyl-L-Carnitine (ALCAR) is L-Carnitine with an acetyl group attached. This allows it to cross the blood-brain barrier. ALCAR is fantastic for brain health, focus, and memory, but it is not the preferred form for muscle loading and fat loss."),
